    <abstract>
      <t>BGP is used as the only routing protocol in some networks today. In such networks, it is useful to get a detailed topology view similar to one available when using link state routing protocols. This document defines extensions to the BGP Link-state (BGP-LS) address- family and the procedures for advertisement of topology information in a BGP-only network.</t>
